28/09/2010
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- The foreign ministry announced on Monday (September 27th) that Turkish patrol boats have fired warning shots at a Greek Cypriot fishing vessel off the coast of northern Cyprus. According to the ministry, the shots were fired in international waters. Authorities say they are investigating the incident and have notified the UN about it. No injuries were reported. (DPA, News.gr - 27/09/10)
